:INFO
The 1007-Page Question: Is the Investment Worth It
The Way of Kings is not a novel you pick up casually. Brandon Sanderson takes \
200 pages to establish characters and world before anything you would call a \
plot arrives. I read it over six weeks, took notes on the cosmology and the \
character arcs, and tracked my page count daily because that is the kind of \
reader this book requires you to be. The answer to whether it is worth it is \
yes, but only if you commit to the kind of reading it is asking for.

